docs.abstract: With a Democratic governor in office, the party was in full control of Virginia state government for the first time in a generation.

docs.lead_paragraph: Democrats completed Virginia’s historic partisan shift from red to blue on Tuesday, winning majorities in both chambers of the legislature and consolidating power across state government for the first time in a generation.
